        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 24 at 2:37PM PDT by NWS Elko NV</headline>
        <description>At 237 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Pass Summit, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Pass Summit.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
